<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="581" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[167,777,933,1235]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,287,933,957]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male imago: 1) blackish marks on thorax and abdomen forming a pair of sublateral longitudinal lines (
<figureCitation box="[177,241,1003,1027]" captionStart="Figures 9–18" captionStartId="3.[168,241,1871,1891]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1846]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 9–18. Dorsal habitus of some species of Leptophlebiidae (Ephemeroptera) found in Maranhão state, Brazil. 9. Askola emmerichi. 10. Farrodes xingu. 11. Fittkaulus cururuensis. 12. Hermanellopsis arsia. 13. Hydromastodon sallesi. 14. Hydrosmilodon gilliesae. 15. Leentvaaria palpalis. 16. Miroculitus emersoni. 17. Miroculis (Atroari) duckensis. 18. Paramaka convexa. Scale bars = 2 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), wings with blackish marks; 2) dorsal portion of eyes grayish and widely meeting dorsally on meson of head (
<figureCitation box="[237,305,1072,1096]" captionStart="Figures 9–18" captionStartId="3.[168,241,1871,1891]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1846]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 9–18. Dorsal habitus of some species of Leptophlebiidae (Ephemeroptera) found in Maranhão state, Brazil. 9. Askola emmerichi. 10. Farrodes xingu. 11. Fittkaulus cururuensis. 12. Hermanellopsis arsia. 13. Hydromastodon sallesi. 14. Hydrosmilodon gilliesae. 15. Leentvaaria palpalis. 16. Miroculitus emersoni. 17. Miroculis (Atroari) duckensis. 18. Paramaka convexa. Scale bars = 2 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); 3) wings with blackish marks with four brown-spotted cross veins basal to bulla; 4) forceps yellowish brown, inner margins whitish (
<figureCitation box="[587,667,1142,1166]" captionStart="Figures 29–47" captionStartId="10.[168,241,1656,1676]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-10@10.[168,1419,160,1632]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 29–47. Genitalia of some species of Leptophlebiidae (Ephemeroptera) found in Maranhão state, Brazil. 29. Askola emmerichi. 30. Farrodes xingu. 31. Hermanellopsis arsia. 32. Hydromastodon sallesi. 33. Hydrosmilodon gilliesae. 34. Leentvaaria palpalis. 35. Miroculitus emersoni. 36. Miroculis (Atroari) duckensis. 37. Paramaka convexa. 38. Simothraulopsis demerara. 39. S. diamantinensis. 40. S. janae. 41. S. sinuosus. 42. Thraulodes luizgonzagai. 43. T. marreroi. 44. T. sternimaculatus. 45. Tikuna bilineata. 46. Traverella maranhensis. 47. Ulmeritoides flavopedes. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); 5) penis extending well beyond posterior margin of styliger plate (
<figureCitation box="[176,254,1211,1235]" captionStart="Figures 29–47" captionStartId="10.[168,241,1656,1676]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-10@10.[168,1419,160,1632]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 29–47. Genitalia of some species of Leptophlebiidae (Ephemeroptera) found in Maranhão state, Brazil. 29. Askola emmerichi. 30. Farrodes xingu. 31. Hermanellopsis arsia. 32. Hydromastodon sallesi. 33. Hydrosmilodon gilliesae. 34. Leentvaaria palpalis. 35. Miroculitus emersoni. 36. Miroculis (Atroari) duckensis. 37. Paramaka convexa. 38. Simothraulopsis demerara. 39. S. diamantinensis. 40. S. janae. 41. S. sinuosus. 42. Thraulodes luizgonzagai. 43. T. marreroi. 44. T. sternimaculatus. 45. Tikuna bilineata. 46. Traverella maranhensis. 47. Ulmeritoides flavopedes. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). (Adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Dominguez E &amp; Molineri C &amp; Mariano R" box="[437,686,1211,1235]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" pagination="29 - 44" refId="ref11150" refString="Dominguez E, Molineri C, Mariano R (2009) Revision of the South American species of Hagenulopsis Ulmer and Askola Peters (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae) with description of six new species. Zootaxa 2142: 29 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2142.1. 3" type="journal article" year="2009">Domínguez et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
